---
title: Maple-And-Mustard-Glazed Pork Chops with Roasted Potatoes and a Green Salad
description: Dinnertime usually means savory, but there are some amazing ways to make it sweet. Like by creating a glaze out of maple syrup, as we’ve done here on these pork chops. It gives you a little bit of breakfast-y comfort while staying perfectly hearty. Pop some cinnamon sweet potatoes and buttery green beans on the side, and you’ve got the best of all worlds.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/maple-glazed-pork-chops-5d3f4bbf.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/maple-glazed-pork-chops-5d892d46035b946f204aaf02-992a8559.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/maple-and-mustard-glazed-pork-chops-5d892d46035b946f204aaf02
time required: 40 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 710 kcal
  fat: 35 g
  saturated fat: 6 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 28 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 810 mg
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon}, half the
@thyme{1/8%ounce} sprigs, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender
and crisped, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, strip ¾ tsp thyme leaves from remaining sprigs (1 1/2 tsp leaves for 4
servings); roughly chop leaves. Cut @lemon{1} into wedges. In a #small bowl{},
combine chopped thyme, @maple syrup{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon},
and @chicken stock concentrate{1}.

Meanwhile, pat @pork chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; prick all over
with a #fork{} or #knife{}. Season pork all over with @autumn spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and sear until browned on both
sides, ~{4-6%minutes} per side (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Pour glaze into pan and let simmer until mixture has thickened and pork is cooked
through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn pork to coat. Remove pan from heat and stir in a
squeeze or two of lemon juice.

In a #large bowl{}, toss together @mixed greens{2%ounce},
@dried cranberries{1%ounce}, @sunflower seeds{1%ounce}, @olive oil{1%tablespoon},
and a squeeze or two of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

Discard thyme sprigs from baking sheet with potatoes. Divide potatoes, pork, and
salad between plates. Drizzle pork with any remaining glaze. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges on the side.